motion.globals:
GLOBAL SETUP — Edwin & Joyce Ormeo Photography homepage (Next.js App Router + Lenis + GSAP ScrollTrigger).

== INSTALL / REGISTER ==
npm i lenis gsap. Use the React wrappers where helpful but drive everything from a single client component (e.g. app/(site)/page.tsx is a Server Component; mount a "use client" <MotionProvider> that owns Lenis + a top-level gsap.context()). Register once, client-side only:
```
'use client';
import { useLayoutEffect, useRef } from 'react';
import Lenis from 'lenis';
import gsap from 'gsap';
import { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger';
gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);
```

== LENIS CONFIG (the single source of scroll truth) ==
```
const lenis = new Lenis({
  duration: 1.15,            // cinematic, weighty but not sludgy
  easing: (t) => Math.min(1, 1.001 - Math.pow(2, -10 * t)), // expo-out
  smoothWheel: true,
  syncTouch: false,          // keep native momentum on touch; smooth only wheel
  wheelMultiplier: 1.0,
  lerp: undefined,           // use duration+easing, not lerp, for filmic feel
});
```
CRITICAL — drive Lenis from GSAP's ticker so scrub stays perfectly in lockstep (no double RAF, no jitter):
```
lenis.on('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update);
gsap.ticker.add((time) => lenis.raf(time * 1000));
gsap.ticker.lagSmoothing(0);
```
Do NOT also call requestAnimationFrame(raf) yourself — the ticker is the only loop. For anchor links use lenis.scrollTo(target, { offset, duration }).

== SCROLLTRIGGER GLOBAL DEFAULTS ==
ScrollTrigger.defaults({ markers: false }); set ScrollTrigger.config({ ignoreMobileResize: true }) to avoid pin jumps when mobile URL bar shows/hides. After all images/fonts load call ScrollTrigger.refresh() (also on the Next.js route ready event and in a ResizeObserver-debounced handler). Because Next streams, gate refresh behind document.fonts.ready and an imagesLoaded pass so pinned heights are measured against final layout.

== CLEANUP (Next.js navigation safe) ==
Wrap all animations in `const ctx = gsap.context(() => { ... }, rootRef)` and return `() => { ctx.revert(); lenis.destroy(); gsap.ticker.remove(rafFn); }`. Reverting the context kills every ScrollTrigger, restores pin-spacing, and removes inline styles so client-side route changes don't leak pins.

== REDUCED MOTION — GLOBAL STRATEGY ==
Use gsap.matchMedia() as the master switch so reduced-motion teardown is automatic on revert:
```
const mm = gsap.matchMedia();
mm.add({
  motionOK: '(prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference)',
  motionReduce: '(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)',
}, (ctx) => {
  const { motionReduce } = ctx.conditions;
  // build full or reduced timelines based on motionReduce
});
```
When motionReduce is true: (1) DESTROY Lenis / never start smooth scroll — let the OS use native scroll; (2) kill ALL pinning (no horizontal pin, no parallax band pin) — sections become normal vertical flow; (3) replace every reveal with a single opacity 0→1 fade at ~0.3s, no transform/scale/clip-path travel; (4) marquees and infinite loops are paused on a static frame; (5) counters jump straight to final value; (6) magnetic cursor disabled, native cursor only; (7) any video autoplay swapped for a still poster. Also respect the Save-Data header and pause all rAF loops via IntersectionObserver / document.hidden so offscreen marquees don't burn battery.

== PERFORMANCE NOTES ==
- Animate only transform + opacity + clip-path (compositor-friendly); never animate top/left/width/height in scrubbed timelines. Set will-change: transform on actively-scrubbing layers and REMOVE it on complete (gsap clearProps or onLeave) to avoid GPU layer bloat.
- Use next/image with priority on the hero, sizes set per layout, and decoding="async"; pre-decode horizontal-gallery + marquee images with img.decode() before building those triggers so pinned scroll never stutters on first paint.
- Cap parallax travel so no image ever reveals its own edge: image height must be (1 + 2*maxParallaxFraction) of its frame; e.g. for ±12% travel, image is 124% of container and centered.
- One shared ScrollTrigger update loop (already wired to Lenis). Prefer scrub: true (frame-synced) over numeric scrub except where a slight catch-up smoothing is desired (scrub: 0.6).
- invalidateOnRefresh: true on every parallax/scrub trigger so values recompute on resize/orientation change.
- Throttle the magnetic cursor with quickTo (gsap.quickTo) instead of per-event tweens.
